        <abstract> 
<p>Sends last chapter of his book in press [<hi rend="italic">Systems of consanguinity and affinity of the human family</hi> vol. 17 in <hi rend="italic">Smithsonian contributions to knowledge</hi> (1871)], which supports CD on man.</p> 
            <p>Ethnology must study the ages of barbarism as the formative portions of man’s physical and mental history.</p>
